      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification against analytical solutions or established benchmarks for relevant element types and loading modes.",
      "rationale": "Each solver was verified against NAFEMS benchmark problems and analytical Euler-Bernoulli beam solutions for bending-dominated loading. Results within 1% of reference solutions for all relevant element formulations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating QoI change less than 5% between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed on the pedicle screw construct geometry. Stiffness QoI varied by 1.8% between the medium and fine mesh levels; yield force varied by 2.3%. Richardson extrapolation confirmed discretization error contribution below 3% for all QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms and energy balance monitored; iterative convergence tolerance documented.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver convergence was monitored via force and displacement residual norms (tolerance 1e-6). Energy balance checked at each load increment. No convergence anomalies observed across all 11 model instances."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented modeling procedure with independent peer review of boundary condition and material assignment steps.",
      "rationale": "A standardized modeling procedure document was developed and followed by all three modeling teams. An independent reviewer from CDRH confirmed boundary condition assignments, contact definitions, and material property inputs prior to final simulation runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model and contact formulation justified by literature and sensitivity to model form choices documented.",
      "rationale": "Isotropic elastic-perfectly-plastic material model for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) justified by published stress-strain characterization data. Coulomb friction contact at screw-rod interface with mu=0.3 consistent with tribological literature. Alternative bilinear kinematic hardening model produced QoI differences below 2%, confirming model form insensitivity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric parameters sourced from traceable measurements with uncertainty bounds documented.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and Poisson ratio (0.34) for Ti-6Al-4V sourced from ASTM F136 and manufacturer material certificates. Geometric dimensions measured from three production screws via CMM with tolerance ±0.01 mm. Input uncertainty propagated through the model using interval arithmetic; combined input uncertainty contribution to QoI uncertainty estimated at ±3.1%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples representative of production geometry; dimensional verification documented.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs sourced from a single production lot. CMM dimensional verification confirmed all screws within drawing tolerances. Constructs assembled by trained technicians following validated assembly procedure to ensure consistent preload."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios or deviation from single-condition testing is justified.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load level per ASTM F1717 protocol. Clinical loading variability across patient body weight and activity level was not replicated experimentally. This factor is below the required level; the shortfall is acknowledged and partially mitigated by the conservative nature of the ASTM F1717 load magnitude relative to in vivo estimates."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters demonstrably equivalent to test article parameters within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FEA model geometry derived directly from CMM measurements of the test articles. Material properties assigned from the same material certificate used to characterize the production lot. Boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture constraints as confirmed by fixture compliance measurements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) below 1.96 for all primary QoIs; percentage difference below 10%.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy both acceptance criteria. E/uval values of 0.87, 1.41, and 1.58 are all below 1.96. Percentage differences of 4.2%, 6.8%, and 7.1% are all below the 10% threshold. Results consistent across both testing laboratories."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to the clinical failure mode and regulatory decision.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly reflect the structural performance attributes relevant to pedicle screw fatigue and fracture risk. These QoIs are the basis for the regulatory submission comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario geometry, loading, and boundary conditions match the COU scenario with documented justification for any differences.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity uses the identical screw geometry, rod diameter, and construct configuration as the COU. ASTM F1717 loading and boundary conditions are the regulatory standard for this device class. The validation scenario is therefore directly representative of the COU without extrapolation."
    }
