    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for a Model Risk Level 3, Medium assurance COU. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged and partially mitigated by the conservative nature of ASTM F1717 loading. All three primary QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw.",
